snippet.textDisplay:
So I was doing the exercise (as well as one could) alongside Ethan and when she said to imagine my younger self, I saw little 10 year old me and she was just...crying. And I started tearing up myself and I imagined hugging her and telling her I was gonna look after her and just...wishing someone had been there for me when i really was that age. 10 to 14 were some of the worst years of my life. I didnt have anyone to protect me, I didn't have anyone I felt I could trust. I wanted to kill myself then, just throw myself into the little river beside my fathers house and be at peace. I saw that little girl who felt so alone and so scared and so empty and I wanted to tell her it would be okay, that we'd survive that and the years afterwards. We'd love some and lose alot and grow and discover new things about ourselves and that by the time we were 22, as I am now, we'd be okay. A little bird who found someone worth living for, who found her passion in creating other worlds and images with paint and clay.
We survived. I survived.
